126
00:07:48,281 --> 00:07:49,680
I see.

127
00:07:49,681 --> 00:07:53,380
Was your room burglarized, sir?

128
00:07:53,381 --> 00:07:55,680
Conan?

129
00:07:55,681 --> 00:07:58,180
What's with this brat?

130
00:07:58,181 --> 00:07:59,580
Well...

131
00:07:59,581 --> 00:08:03,180
There's a scratch on the keyhole of the door,

132
00:08:03,181 --> 00:08:04,781
so I thought that maybe...

133
00:08:05,781 --> 00:08:06,881
Really?

134
00:08:08,381 --> 00:08:09,980
True.

135
00:08:09,981 --> 00:08:12,880
Maybe it's just a prank.

136
00:08:12,881 --> 00:08:15,180
Nothing was stolen either.

137
00:08:15,181 --> 00:08:17,880
Please check carefully once more.

138
00:08:17,881 --> 00:08:20,180
And if you find something suspicious...

139
00:08:20,181 --> 00:08:21,780
Then,

140
00:08:21,781 --> 00:08:24,481
Will you show us the veranda of your room?

141
00:08:28,881 --> 00:08:31,481
Do you mind if we check your veranda?

142
00:08:50,181 --> 00:08:52,180
Did you find anything?

143
00:08:52,181 --> 00:08:54,080
No, nothing in particular.

144
00:08:54,081 --> 00:08:56,581
Thank you for your cooperation.

145
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:02,080
Conan, let's go.

146
00:09:02,081 --> 00:09:03,081
What's the matter?

147
00:09:03,082 --> 00:09:04,880
I have to use the restroom.

148
00:09:04,881 --> 00:09:07,581
I was holding it from some time ago.

149
00:09:09,081 --> 00:09:12,080
I'm sorry but could he use your restroom?

150
00:09:12,081 --> 00:09:13,780
Go ahead. Its...

151
00:09:13,781 --> 00:09:15,981
I'm fine. I know.

152
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:27,080
Conan, here we are.

153
00:09:27,081 --> 00:09:30,381
I'm sorry. I was thinking of something.

154
00:09:31,981 --> 00:09:34,381
Inspector Megure, I'm back.

155
00:09:36,281 --> 00:09:38,180
Is something wrong?

156
00:09:38,181 --> 00:09:40,580
We found the perpetrator.

157
00:09:40,581 --> 00:09:43,880
The perpetrator? Wasn't this an accident?

158
00:09:43,881 --> 00:09:45,380
Yeah, no...

159
00:09:45,381 --> 00:09:47,580
That's not it.

160
00:09:47,581 --> 00:09:51,280
This necklace seems to be Mrs. Miyosh's but...

161
00:09:51,281 --> 00:09:53,980
My boyfriend bought it for me when we were abroad,

162
00:09:53,981 --> 00:09:55,180
so there's no mistake about it.

163
00:09:55,181 --> 00:09:57,980
What about it?

164
00:09:57,981 --> 00:10:01,380
That necklace came out from this room.

165
00:10:01,381 --> 00:10:03,980
What? Then, don't tell me that...

166
00:10:03,981 --> 00:10:09,580
Yeah. In other words the perpetrator who burglarized this area

167
00:10:09,581 --> 00:10:11,580
is a resident of this room got drunk,

168
00:10:11,581 --> 00:10:14,480
and fell to his death from the veranda.

169
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:17,181
His name was Naotsugu Kitagami!

170
00:10:19,581 --> 00:10:23,580
And how did the interrogation go, Officer Takagi?

171
00:10:23,581 --> 00:10:24,780
Well...

172
00:10:24,781 --> 00:10:27,580
We didn't get a hold of any useful information.

173
00:10:27,581 --> 00:10:28,880
I see.

174
00:10:28,881 --> 00:10:31,380
So just as Mr. Mouri said,

175
00:10:31,381 --> 00:10:33,580
he got drunk and fell to his death.

176
00:10:33,581 --> 00:10:35,081
The case is settled.

177
00:10:36,581 --> 00:10:39,680
I see, I get the picture.

178
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:43,081
This is not a mere death fall case.

179
00:10:46,793 --> 00:10:49,292
About the stolen objects and burglary,

180
00:10:49,293 --> 00:10:51,992
