270
00:15:06,993 --> 00:15:10,093
having killed Mr. Kitagami.

271
00:15:11,893 --> 00:15:13,192
What?

272
00:15:13,193 --> 00:15:15,392
I don't know what you're talking about.

273
00:15:15,393 --> 00:15:17,892
Mr. Mouri. Just what're you talking about?

274
00:15:17,893 --> 00:15:20,492
Mr. Kitagami got drunk,

275
00:15:20,493 --> 00:15:24,492
tripped over the liquor bottle and fell off the veranda of his room.

276
00:15:24,493 --> 00:15:27,892
Yeah, that's what you said.

277
00:15:27,893 --> 00:15:31,592
There were scrape marks all over the body of the corpse.

278
00:15:31,593 --> 00:15:36,192
But, there were no scratches on his veranda that matched those marks.

279
00:15:36,193 --> 00:15:38,592
Isn't that because the scratches found on him

280
00:15:38,593 --> 00:15:41,492
were scrapes made when he fell to the ground?

281
00:15:41,493 --> 00:15:45,092
Officer Takagi, please check the veranda of this room.

282
00:15:45,093 --> 00:15:46,992
There should be scratch marks.

283
00:15:46,993 --> 00:15:47,993
Yes, sir!

284
00:15:55,193 --> 00:15:57,492
Mr. Mouri, yes, there are!

285
00:15:57,493 --> 00:16:00,592
New scrape marks.

286
00:16:00,593 --> 00:16:04,492
Mr. Sawada, after killing Mr. Kitagami,

287
00:16:04,493 --> 00:16:07,692
you probably tried to throw him over your veranda.

288
00:16:07,693 --> 00:16:12,192
But, it's not easy throwing someone over.

289
00:16:12,193 --> 00:16:15,292
That's why in order to throw Mr. Kitagami over the veranda,

290
00:16:15,293 --> 00:16:17,792
you carried him up to the railing once.

291
00:16:17,793 --> 00:16:20,792
When you did so, the buckle of Mr. Kitagami's belt

292
00:16:20,793 --> 00:16:24,092
rubbed against the railing and scratched it.

293
00:16:24,093 --> 00:16:27,692
And of course, you'll scrape marks on Mr. Kitagami's belt buckle too.

294
00:16:27,693 --> 00:16:30,892
Then, you lifted his legs up and dropped him slowly.

295
00:16:30,893 --> 00:16:34,793
That's when he got scrape marks all over the front part of his body.

296
00:16:35,893 --> 00:16:38,392
How rude can you get?

297
00:16:38,393 --> 00:16:39,892
Barging in like this

298
00:16:39,893 --> 00:16:41,692
then saying that I'm a murderer?

299
00:16:41,693 --> 00:16:45,692
The guy called Kitagami fell off his own veranda, right?

300
00:16:45,693 --> 00:16:49,392
It could be that he scraped his body against the wall of this veranda

301
00:16:49,393 --> 00:16:50,992
when he went falling, no?

302
00:16:50,993 --> 00:16:55,392
Besides, in the first place, why do I have to kill him?

303
00:16:55,393 --> 00:16:58,092
I never even really talked to him too.

304
00:16:58,093 --> 00:16:59,492
Motive...

305
00:16:59,493 --> 00:17:01,592
Mr. Mouri, how about it?

306
00:17:01,593 --> 00:17:05,392
Mr. Kitagami was a burglar.

307
00:17:05,393 --> 00:17:10,293
And there are traces of this door having been picked.

308
00:17:11,693 --> 00:17:13,492
Then, don't tell me that...

309
00:17:13,493 --> 00:17:17,792
Yes, he burglarized this room.

310
00:17:17,793 --> 00:17:19,992
And coincidentally ran into you

311
00:17:19,993 --> 00:17:22,292
when you came home.

312
00:17:22,293 --> 00:17:25,792
Are you saying that he happened to run into the burgler in his place

313
00:17:25,793 --> 00:17:28,492
and inadvertently killed him?

314
00:17:28,493 --> 00:17:29,692
Yes.

315
00:17:29,693 --> 00:17:31,392
But, Mr. Mouri...

316
00:17:31,393 --> 00:17:36,492
Why didn't Mr. Sawada report it to the police or flee?

317
00:17:36,493 --> 00:17:40,192
What if it's not that he didn't but rather couldn't?

318
00:17:40,193 --> 00:17:41,792
He couldn't?

319
00:17:41,793 --> 00:17:43,292
Why not?

320
00:17:43,293 --> 00:17:45,593
I think I know why.

321
00:17:47,093 --> 00:17:49,392
When I borrowed the restroom here,

322
00:17:49,393 --> 00:17:52,892
there was a big bag shoved into the cabinet.

323
00:17:52,893 --> 00:17:54,992
-You brat! -Come, come, now...

324
00:17:54,993 --> 00:17:58,092
Officer Takagi, will you bring that bag over here.

325
00:17:58,093 --> 00:17:59,292
Yes, sir!

326
00:17:59,293 --> 00:18:01,293
You don't mind, do you?

327
00:18:02,493 --> 00:18:04,292
Inspector Megure.

328
00:18:04,293 --> 00:18:07,192
Just as Conan said, the bag was there.

329
00:18:07,193 --> 00:18:08,493
And the contents?

330
00:18:10,993 --> 00:18:11,993
What?

331
00:18:11,994 --> 00:18:13,092
This is...

332
00:18:13,093 --> 00:18:15,792
Mr. Sawada, excuse me

333
00:18:15,793 --> 00:18:18,992
but you don't look to be someone who would have enough money

334
00:18:18,993 --> 00:18:21,392
to own valuable things like these.

335
00:18:21,393 --> 00:18:23,592
What on earth are these?

336
00:18:23,593 --> 00:18:25,093
How about it?

337
00:18:26,093 --> 00:18:27,492
Oh, right.

338
00:18:27,493 --> 00:18:30,892
Those valuables are the ones that I robbed!

339
00:18:30,893 --> 00:18:35,492
Mr. Kitagami, who broke in here found these valuables

340
00:18:35,493 --> 00:18:37,992
so you killed to shut him up.

341
00:18:37,993 --> 00:18:39,692
Wrong!

342
00:18:39,693 --> 00:18:42,092
It's true that I panicked when he found them

343
00:18:42,093 --> 00:18:43,492
but I made a deal with him.

344
00:18:43,493 --> 00:18:44,692
A deal?

345
00:18:44,693 --> 00:18:47,392
Since he found the valuables,

346
00:18:47,393 --> 00:18:49,992
I gave him a piece.

347
00:18:49,993 --> 00:18:52,292
With that we decided that I would forget

348
00:18:52,293 --> 00:18:55,392
about the fact that he was a burglar

349
00:18:55,393 --> 00:18:58,692
and he would forget that I was a robber. Then, he left.

350
00:18:58,693 --> 00:19:02,892
I know nothing about him falling to his death!

351
00:19:02,893 --> 00:19:05,292
Enough with delusive stories!

352
00:19:05,293 --> 00:19:11,092
Mr. Mouri, I hope your deduction is based on proof.

353
00:19:11,093 --> 00:19:13,892
Of course. Besides the valuables,

354
00:19:13,893 --> 00:19:17,692
there is pepper spray in that bag.

355
00:19:17,693 --> 00:19:20,392
I guess you used it when robbing.

356
00:19:20,393 --> 00:19:23,192
Mr. Kitagami's eyelids were red and swollen,

357
00:19:23,193 --> 00:19:24,792
not because of the liquor

358
00:19:24,793 --> 00:19:27,793
but because pepper spray was used on him.

359
00:19:28,793 --> 00:19:30,692
That won't serve as proof.

360
00:19:30,693 --> 00:19:32,092
Mr. Mouri.

361
00:19:32,093 --> 00:19:35,292
I borrowed what you asked for from forensics.

362
00:19:35,293 --> 00:19:38,792
Good. Conan, please help me.

363
00:19:38,793 --> 00:19:39,893
Okay!

364
00:19:42,093 --> 00:19:45,393
Officer Takagi, may borrow that?

365
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:47,393
Yeah.

366
00:19:47,394 --> 00:19:50,892
When using this type of spray,

367
00:19:50,893 --> 00:19:54,893
it sprays a bit on the user too.

368
00:19:56,193 --> 00:20:00,392
Since the fluid's transparent, it's hard to tell.

369
00:20:00,393 --> 00:20:01,892
Don't worry.

370
00:20:01,893 --> 00:20:04,592
UV coating is used in pepper sprays

371
00:20:04,593 --> 00:20:09,892
so that the perpetrator who flees can be pursued!

372
00:20:09,893 --> 00:20:13,992
So Officer Chiba, will you turn off the light of the room?

373
00:20:13,993 --> 00:20:14,993
Yeah.

374
00:20:16,993 --> 00:20:20,592
Officer Chiba, can you shine the black light on my hand

375
00:20:20,593 --> 00:20:22,493
and Conan's clothes?

376
00:20:26,293 --> 00:20:27,992
See?

377
00:20:27,993 --> 00:20:29,892
I see.

378
00:20:29,893 --> 00:20:31,592
Which means...

379
00:20:31,593 --> 00:20:36,592
If Mr. Sawada's sleeve glows like Conan's clothes...

380
00:20:36,593 --> 00:20:38,593
Excuse me.

381
00:20:41,293 --> 00:20:44,793
How about it? Do you still insist you didn't do it?

382
00:20:46,493 --> 00:20:49,792
He said that he changed his mind

383
00:20:49,793 --> 00:20:52,793
and suddenly demanded to have all the valuables.

384
00:20:53,993 --> 00:20:56,992
He overwhelmingly came at me

385
00:20:56,993 --> 00:21:00,692
so I impulsively sprayed him with the pepper spray that was in the bag.

386
00:21:00,693 --> 00:21:01,992
He squirmed around because it stung,

387
00:21:01,993 --> 00:21:04,192
his feet tripped over the table

388
00:21:04,193 --> 00:21:07,992
and he hit his head on the corner of the shelf.

389
00:21:07,993 --> 00:21:11,192
He barged in here on his own and died on his own!

390
00:21:11,193 --> 00:21:14,292
Why do I have to take responsibility for this?

391
00:21:14,293 --> 00:21:17,192
Since I realized he lived right above me,

392
00:21:17,193 --> 00:21:18,492
I figured it wouldn't look unnatural

393
00:21:18,493 --> 00:21:20,692
even if I dropped him from this veranda.

394
00:21:20,693 --> 00:21:23,692
Besides, I had the key to his room too.

395
00:21:23,693 --> 00:21:27,292
You tried to cover up your crime.

396
00:21:27,293 --> 00:21:29,292
You idiot!

397
00:21:29,293 --> 00:21:31,992
On top of robbing jewels,

398
00:21:31,993 --> 00:21:33,392
you threw Mr. Kitagami off the veranda

399
00:21:33,393 --> 00:21:37,192
and tried to use childish measures to cover up your crime.

400
00:21:37,193 --> 00:21:39,193
Do you understand the seriousness of the crime you committed?

401
00:21:40,893 --> 00:21:42,593
Darn.

402
00:21:44,093 --> 00:21:46,493
Darn!

403
00:23:11,993 --> 00:23:14,592
It's about time you get up, Mr. Mouri.

404
00:23:14,593 --> 00:23:16,593
We're leaving.

405
00:23:20,793 --> 00:23:21,893
Where am I?

406
00:23:29,693 --> 00:23:32,392
My eyes! My eyes! My eyes!

407
00:23:32,393 --> 00:23:35,392
Something's on my hand...

408
00:23:35,393 --> 00:23:36,792
Your deduction was superb,

409
00:23:36,793 --> 00:23:39,092
but how unsightly of you now.

410
00:23:39,093 --> 00:23:40,993
You've got to take care of your eyes.

411
00:23:43,393 --> 00:23:44,793
"Next Episode" -Koji Haneda.

412
00:23:46,293 --> 00:23:48,992
Shards of glass?

413
00:23:48,993 --> 00:23:50,792
There's a pattern and letters on it.

414
00:23:50,793 --> 00:23:53,192
It probably spelt...

415
00:23:53,193 --> 00:23:55,092
"Put On Mascara".

416
00:23:55,093 --> 00:23:56,692
So what?

417
00:23:56,693 --> 00:24:00,092
Are you saying that I'm the one who did it?

418
00:24:00,093 --> 00:24:01,992
I'd like to go

419
00:24:01,993 --> 00:24:06,093
to the crime site too.

420
00:24:06,993 --> 00:24:08,692
Next Conan,

421
00:24:08,693 --> 00:24:12,293
"The Same Crime Scene as 17 Years Ago (Part 1)"

